# Solver-sweep config queue. One JSON object per line. Blank lines and lines starting
# with '#' are ignored, so you can comment-out or reorder configs by hand.
#
# Fields: label (str), floor (bool), target (int), weight (int), runs (int repeats),
#         budget (optional [P0,P1,P2,P3] seconds; defaults to [900,300,300,2400]).
#
# Each line expands to `runs` separately-snapshotted solves: label-r1, label-r2, ...
# Editing floor/target/weight/budget makes it a NEW unit (param hash changes), so it
# re-runs; re-ordering or commenting-out already-DONE units is safe.
#
# --- Rounds 3-5 (DONE, 2026-06-22/23) — kept for history; PRE-FIX, do not re-run ---
# Round 3: floor-OFF/target=2; fill 75-120 curve; w95 emerged as lead (fragile=4 both draws).
# Round 4: confirm w95 fragile=4 stable + probes at 85/110.
# Round 5: P3=4000 + many repeats to test how OFTEN each weight reaches the low (~882) plateau.
# #{"label":"cfgR5-01","floor":false,"target":2,"weight":95,"runs":7,"budget":[900,300,300,4000]}
# #{"label":"cfgR5-02","floor":false,"target":2,"weight":75,"runs":5,"budget":[900,300,300,4000]}
# #{"label":"cfgR5-03","floor":false,"target":2,"weight":110,"runs":4,"budget":[900,300,300,4000]}
